Our Mission

is to help our clients live a better life at home through consistent delivery of quality home care.

Medical Service Company provides the best solutions for affordable and trustworthy Home Care in San Diego, Encinitas, Del Mar, Oceanside, Rancho Santa Fe, Carlsbad, and Solana Beach.

We thoroughly screen, bond and insure all of our Home Care professionals including caregivers, certified nursing assistants and Home Care aides.

Call Now (619) 555-0100

Medical Service Company

Meet Lauren Reynolds

“When my mother was diagnosed with aggressive and terminal breast cancer at age 56, she asked us to promise that she could spend the rest of her days in the comfort of her own home. We worked hard to make that happen for my mother. We’d be honored to make that happen for you or the person you love.”

Lauren Reynolds, Former Award Winning 10News Anchor/Investigative Reporter, who founded Medical Service Company after her own experience helping her mother stay safe and comfortable at home.

Medical Service Company is licensed and accredited by the Accreditation Commission for Health Care to provide quality home care.

Accreditation is a voluntary extra step earned by meeting stringent national standards for quality, client satisfaction and safety. Accredited services include:
companion/homemaker, personal care attendant, in home nursing and infusion services.

Our caring and professional caregivers help with bathing, dressing, transfers, safety monitoring, meal preparation, errands and medication reminders and light housekeeping. Nurses assist with case management, medication administration, wound care, feeding tubes, injections and more. Care is offered hourly, daily, and around the clock.

Free In-Home

"Needs Evaluation"

 No-Cost, No Obligation "Needs Evaluation"

We are happy to send a specially trained team member to visit you at your home, hospital room or rehabilitation center for a no-cost "Needs Evaluation" to see what kind of care would be best for you or someone you love. This is a no-obligation meeting.

If you decide to hire us for quality home care, the next step is that our Nursing Supervisor performs a thorough evaluation, creates a detailed "person centered" care plan and works with you to make sure all of your care needs are met.
